ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course introduce the major principle in modern crystallography. If you want to do structure biology in the future, you should take it.
I would recommend this class to other students. I thought it was a really good class and it gave a really thorough introduction to protein crystallography.
I would.but I hear the professors will change next year so who knows if my recommendation will be valid.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I will do structure biology in the future. Therefore, this course is a necessity for my future disseration.
This course was a valuable contribution because it provided a great deal of information about crystallography which will most likely be extremely useful for my understanding of my research.
